Articulatory Analysis

Tabea Thies

2022-09-13

Comparing levoDOPA and DBS effect on tongue body movements

Load necessary packages

library(tidyverse)
library(ggplot2)
library(lme4)
library(lmerTest)
library(merTools)
library(sjPlot)
library(sjmisc)

Load data set

data <- read_csv('../data/articulation.csv')

Create subset for the comparison med-OFF vs med-ON vs DBS-ON

med-OFF functions as baseline here

data_red <-  filter(data, med_con %in% c('med-OFF', 'med-ON', 'med-OFF/DBS-ON'))

## second subset for stats

data_red2 <-  filter(data, med_con %in% c('med-OFF', 'med-OFF/DBS-ON'))

Movement duration

Descriptive stats for reporting values in Section 9.2.3

DUR_stats <- data_red %>% 
  group_by(med_con) %>% 
  summarise(M = round(mean(GAI_V1)),
            SD = round(sd(GAI_V1)))

Plot tongue body movement duration

DUR_stats2 %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=factor(med_con, level = c("med-ON", "med-OFF", "med-OFF/DBS-ON")), y=M, group = focus_con, col=focus_con)) + 
  geom_line(size = 2) +
  geom_point(size = 14)+
  theme_classic() +
  theme(legend.position = 'none')+
  theme(legend.title = element_blank(),
        legend.text = element_text(size = 36))+
  scale_color_manual(values = c("#8da0cb", "#66c2a5", "#fc8d62")) +
  xlab(NULL) +
  scale_x_discrete(labels = c('med-ON','baseline', "DBS-ON"))+
  coord_cartesian(ylim = c(175, 210)) + 
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(180, 210, 10)) +
  ylab("Duration (ms)")+
  theme(axis.title.y = element_text(face = 'bold', size = 42, margin = margin(r = 30)))+
  theme(strip.text.x = element_text(size=38, face="bold"),
        strip.background = element_blank())+
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(size = 36),
        axis.text.y = element_text(size = 36)) +
  theme(axis.ticks.x = element_blank(), 
        axis.ticks.y = element_blank())

Create linear mixed model to investigate effect on TB duration

mdl <- lmer(GAI_V1 ~ med_con + focus_con + vowel + cons + age  + (1 + focus_con+med_con|speaker), data_red2, REML = FALSE)

Explore random effects with function REsim

Effects for individual levels are simulated
Output: mean, median and sd of the random effect estimates

Plots estimated random effects for each participant
95 % Intervals that do not overlap zero are bold

randoms <- REsim(mdl) 
plotREsim(randoms)

Plot estimated 95 % interval spans for the intercept of TB duration

random2 <- subset(randoms, term == "(Intercept)")

random2 %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = mean, xmin = mean-sd-sd, xmax = mean+sd+sd, y = reorder(groupID, mean))) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0, linetype = 'dashed') +
  geom_point(size = 5)+
  geom_errorbar(size = 1) +
  theme_classic()+
  xlab('95 % intervals of estimated random intercepts for TB duration') +
  ylab('Speaker')+
  theme(axis.title.y = element_text(face = 'bold', size = 18, margin = margin(r = 12)))+
  theme(axis.title.x = element_text(face = 'bold', size = 18, margin = margin(t = 12)))+
  theme(strip.text.x = element_text(size=18, face="bold"),
        strip.background = element_blank())+
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(size = 18),
        axis.text.y = element_text(size = 18)) +
  theme(axis.ticks.x = element_blank(), 
        axis.ticks.y = element_blank())+
  theme(legend.position = "top",
        legend.title = element_blank(),
        legend.text = element_text(size = 18))
